<div id="pf58f" class="pf w1c h124" data-page-no="58f"><div class="pc pc58f w1c h124"><div class="t m1755 x18 h28 y1b59 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3</div><div class="t m666 x5d h28 y1b59 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2 </div><div class="t m5 x74 h4 y1b59 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"></div><div class="t m14c4 x85 h4 y1e75 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ACTS OP &apos;EWE APOSTLES, </div><div class="t mb27 x26 h28 y1f8e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">point onward he says &quot;we&quot; again; what does this show ? </div><div class="t m767 x26 h28 y1c74 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Compare verses 13, 14. </div><div class="t m13e x74 h28 y19ae ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m1b4 xc5 h28 y19ae ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Since Paul was so anxious to get to Jerusalem, why </div><div class="t m23c x26 h28 y1c77 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">should he have tarried at Troas </div><div class="t m18d x52 h2c y1c77 ff6 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">just seven days? </div><div class="t me29 x7f h28 y215e ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Does </div><div class="t m1ca x26 h28 y20d7 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the time when he arrived there, throw any light on this? </div><div class="t m142 x74 h28 y215f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m23a xc5 h28 y215f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Note the harmony of the narrative throughout. </div><div class="t m9e0 x26 h28 y18c2 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Paul was anxious to get to Jerusalem; having been </div><div class="t m4b6 x26 h28 y1da3 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">hindered by the slowness of the vessel from spending </div><div class="t m96c x26 h28 y164f ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the Sabbath that he had designed to with the church </div><div class="t made x26 h28 y17b3 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">at Troas, he waited there seven days, so that he could </div><div class="t m5ce x26 h28 y20de ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">spend one Sabbath with them; yet in order to lose no </div><div class="t m418 x26 h28 y2160 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">more time than was absolutely necessary, he sent his </div><div class="t m2b2 x26 h28 y1c93 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">traveling companions on with the boat as soon as the </div><div class="t m8b8 x26 h28 y20b6 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath was past, while he himself remained to hold </div><div class="t mbd8 x26 h28 y1d02 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">one last meeting, knowing that he could overtake the </div><div class="t m2b0 x26 h28 y1d1b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">others by a shorter route the next morning on foot. </div><div class="t m417 x6f h31 y642 ff1 fs17 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON XII.—March 19, 1898. </div><div class="t m247 x4e h32 y1f6d ff1 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">MEETING WITH THE ELDERS OF EPHESUS. </div><div class="t m1648 x32 h2f y19bf ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Acts </div><div class="t m190e x3a h8f y1d21 ff2 fs9 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">20 : </div><div class="t m236d x2f h4 y1d21 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">17-38.) </div><div class="t m988 x36 h4 y1d61 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t ma38 x5b h4 y1d61 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">GIVE </div><div class="t m105c x10 h28 y1d61 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">an account of the night meeting at Troas. </div><div class="t m136 x36 h28 y1c62 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t mbbc x5b h28 y1c62 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">How did it happen that a meeting was held at </div><div class="t m6a0 x18 h28 y2161 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that time ? </div><div class="t m139 x36 h28 y1fa4 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m747 x5b h28 y1b1b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">State the course of the journey from that point </div><div class="t me08 x18 h28 y17c4 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">onward. </div><div class="t m13e x36 h28 y1c3d ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m6a4 x5b h28 y17c5 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">From what place did Paul send for the elders of </div><div class="t ma3f x18 h28 y1f2b ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the church at Ephesus to come to him? </div><div class="t m1084 x55 h13 y1e00 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"